delivered to me. too.

274
00:25:25.211 --> 00:25:26.225
Last night.

275
00:25:26.298 --> 00:25:28.120
And I won't see anyone
again till next month.

276
00:25:30.071 --> 00:25:31.729
Why all the trouble?

277
00:25:31.798 --> 00:25:34.163
Well. he's afraid
of the girl.

278
00:25:34.229 --> 00:25:38.220
You know. I mean.
of--of Mrs.Porter.

279
00:25:38.291 --> 00:25:40.527
I mean. that's how
it looks to me.

280
00:25:48.429 --> 00:25:50.849
Look. I don't know
nothing about this. OK?

281
00:25:50.923 --> 00:25:52.778
I know Val
from the old days.

282
00:25:52.843 --> 00:25:55.360
3 months ago he shows up.
asks me to do him a favor.

283
00:25:55.431 --> 00:25:57.220
I make an extra
grand a month...

284
00:25:57.287 --> 00:25:58.813
so I figure.
what the hell. right?

285
00:25:58.886 --> 00:26:01.251
Now you come around
threatening to kill me?

286
00:26:01.317 --> 00:26:02.778
Believe me. that much
a buddy of Val's...

287
00:26:02.852 --> 00:26:04.129
I am not.

288
00:26:04.195 --> 00:26:05.820
He's in the city.
That's all I know.

289
00:26:05.890 --> 00:26:07.264
I got a game going on.

290
00:26:07.330 --> 00:26:09.303
How do you know that?

291
00:26:09.375 --> 00:26:10.749
He said so.

292
00:26:10.815 --> 00:26:12.407
- When?
- When he-- Then.

293
00:26:12.478 --> 00:26:13.851
When he came around.

294
00:26:13.916 --> 00:26:15.345
Said he squared himself
with the syndicate...

295
00:26:15.421 --> 00:26:17.274
said he was back
in the big time.

296
00:26:17.339 --> 00:26:19.705
Back for good.
He was very excited.

297
00:26:19.769 --> 00:26:23.116
Well. you tell him
that Porter is back. too...

298
00:26:23.191 --> 00:26:25.394
and Porter wants his money.

299
00:26:25.462 --> 00:26:27.828
Or I'll pay you a visit
when these kids are not around.

300
00:26:27.893 --> 00:26:28.907
Well--

301
00:26:31.890 --> 00:26:33.434
When would
I tell him this?!

302
00:26:53.646 --> 00:26:55.468
Talk to me.

303
00:26:55.534 --> 00:26:57.388
There's a young lady
to see you. sir.

304
00:26:57.453 --> 00:26:59.426
Her name is Pearl.

305
00:26:59.498 --> 00:27:01.188
She's got 2 very bad habits.

306
00:27:01.258 --> 00:27:04.420
Right now I'm only
interested in one of them.

307
00:27:04.488 --> 00:27:06.113
Heh-heh. Send her up.

308
00:27:09.381 --> 00:27:11.649
Apartment 7 18.
ma'am.

309
00:27:11.715 --> 00:27:13.056
Go right on up.

310
00:27:31.384 --> 00:27:33.041
Send her up.
What's the problem?

311
00:27:33.110 --> 00:27:36.142
Hey. Val. it's Haskell.
Sorry to call you at home.

312
00:27:36.214 --> 00:27:38.480
Don't be sorry. sweetie.
Just don't call.

313
00:27:38.547 --> 00:27:40.456
I thought it
might be important.

314
00:27:40.530 --> 00:27:42.601
I got a call from a cab guy
out in the south end.

315
00:27:42.672 --> 00:27:43.566
What is it?

316
00:27:43.632 --> 00:27:45.486
- It's Stegman.

317
00:27:45.551 --> 00:27:46.630
Shit.
Hold on a second.

318
00:27:52.618 --> 00:27:54.559
Unh!

319
00:27:54.633 --> 00:27:56.420
On your knees.
bitch.

320
00:27:56.489 --> 00:27:58.821
I want satisfaction.

321
00:27:58.887 --> 00:28:01.155
I'm on the phone.
Pearl.

322
00:28:01.222 --> 00:28:02.911
Unh!

323
00:28:04.356 --> 00:28:06.721
That's Mistress Pearl.
you piece of dogshit.

324
00:28:06.786 --> 00:28:08.574
I'm on
the fucking phone!

325
00:28:08.641 --> 00:28:10.331
Ooh!

326
00:28:11.967 --> 00:28:14.715
Ahem.
Make it quick. huh?

327
00:28:14.781 --> 00:28:17.081
Anyhow.
this guy Stegman called.

328
00:28:17.147 --> 00:28:19.033
Sounded all nervous.

329
00:28:19.099 --> 00:28:21.552
Sounded like something
scared the shit out of him.

330
00:28:21.625 --> 00:28:23.031
He said
he had to talk to you.

331
00:28:23.096 --> 00:28:25.583
I said I'd see
what I could do. Val.

332
00:28:25.655 --> 00:28:27.661
Yeah? Did he tell
you what it was about?

333
00:28:27.734 --> 00:28:29.423
He said to tell you
Lynn was dead.

334
00:28:29.492 --> 00:28:31.629
Said some guy came
around talking mean...

335
00:28:31.698 --> 00:28:33.105
and wanted you.

336
00:28:33.170 --> 00:28:36.037
That's all he said.
Thought you oughta know.

337
00:28:36.112 --> 00:28:37.802
Yeah.
you did right.

338
00:28:37.871 --> 00:28:39.365
I want to talk to
that son of a bitch.

339
00:28:39.438 --> 00:28:41.891
Who. Stegman?

340
00:28:41.964 --> 00:28:45.061
No. President Nixon.
Of course Stegman.

341
00:28:45.131 --> 00:28:47.747
Tell him Varrick's
by the bridge.

342
00:28:47.816 --> 00:28:50.663
Make it... Hmm...

343
00:28:50.727 --> 00:28:53.115
make it
20 minutes. huh?

344
00:28:53.190 --> 00:28:54.944
Can't you see
I'm working here?

345
00:29:00.610 --> 00:29:01.754
Unh!

346
00:29:01.824 --> 00:29:03.896
Can't you see
I'm working here?

347
00:29:03.968 --> 00:29:05.341
Oh. yeah.

348
00:29:07.773 --> 00:29:08.982
Put it on
my tab.

349
00:29:09.051 --> 00:29:11.635
I'm looking for a girl.

350
00:29:11.706 --> 00:29:14.072
She goes by
the name of Rosie.

351
00:29:14.137 --> 00:29:15.827
Here's a picture of her.
You know her?

352
00:29:18.487 --> 00:29:21.202
She worked by telephone.
Wouldn't be freelance.

353
00:29:21.268 --> 00:29:24.114
Probably connected
with the syndicate.

354
00:29:24.179 --> 00:29:27.112
Outta my league.
I wouldn't know her.

355
00:29:27.184 --> 00:29:29.517
Well...

356
00:29:29.583 --> 00:29:31.143
maybe you know
somebody who would.

357
00:29:37.195 --> 00:29:39.016
Why you looking for her?

358
00:29:39.082 --> 00:29:40.707
I'm her brother.
I got cancer.

359
00:29:40.776 --> 00:29:42.630
I want to see her
one last time.

360
00:29:42.696 --> 00:29:44.418
You know how it is.

361
00:29:48.451 --> 00:29:50.141
Yeah. you two look close.

362
00:29:53.313 --> 00:29:54.425
Got a cigarette?

363
00:29:59.805 --> 00:30:03.064
Your sister sounds expensive.

364
00:30:03.131 --> 00:30:06.293
Try Michael. bartender
at the Regal Hotel.

365
00:30:07.353 --> 00:30:09.523
That wasn't the name
I was looking for.

366
00:30:09.592 --> 00:30:12.688
It's the only one I got.

367
00:30:38.405 --> 00:30:39.778
Steggie.

368
00:30:39.843 --> 00:30:41.305
Hey. pal. you know.
I tried to call you...

369
00:30:41.379 --> 00:30:43.167
but you must have changed
your number again.

370
00:30:43.234 --> 00:30:44.215
I got nothing.

371
00:30:44.289 --> 00:30:46.709
I never gave you
my original number.

372
00:30:48.095 --> 00:30:49.371
What did this guy
look like?

373
00:30:49.438 --> 00:30:53.330
Well. he had. like.
dark hair. blue eyes.

374
00:30:53.404 --> 00:30:56.021
He was a real
Cro-Magnon-looking bastard.

375
00:30:56.091 --> 00:30:57.018
If Lynn's dead...

376
00:30:57.082 --> 00:30:58.772
maybe he did us
a favor. huh?

377
00:30:58.841 --> 00:31:00.150
I know what you mean...

378
00:31:00.216 --> 00:31:01.263
except I'm out
like a grand a month.

379
00:31:01.336 --> 00:31:03.919
Maybe we can work
something out.

380
00:31:03.989 --> 00:31:05.417
Did you get a name?

381
00:31:05.493 --> 00:31:07.913
Mmm. He said
his name was Porter.

382
00:31:09.202 --> 00:31:10.990
Whoa. whoa. whoa.

383
00:31:11.057 --> 00:31:13.544
He said he was there
for Porter?

384
00:31:13.617 --> 00:31:16.036
No. He said he was Porter.

385
00:31:20.619 --> 00:31:21.633
Yeah.

386
00:31:21.707 --> 00:31:22.949
I'll tell you something.

387
00:31:23.017 --> 00:31:24.872
I wouldn't want that guy
after me. either.

388
00:31:24.937 --> 00:31:26.462
I know how you must feel.

389
00:31:26.537 --> 00:31:28.543
What am l. a nobody?

390
00:31:28.616 --> 00:31:29.791
No.

391
00:31:29.861 --> 00:31:30.941
I've got friends.

392
00:31:31.013 --> 00:31:32.899
All I have to do
is point.

393
00:31:32.963 --> 00:31:34.076
I pick up a phone.
say his name...

394
00:31:34.147 --> 00:31:35.040
and he's a dead man.

395
00:31:35.107 --> 00:31:37.015
And this time
he stays dead!

396
00:31:37.089 --> 00:31:38.812
Val. try to keep it down.

397
00:31:38.881 --> 00:31:40.406
All right?

398
00:31:40.480 --> 00:31:41.908
It's OK.

399
00:31:41.982 --> 00:31:43.770
What did he say
about me?

400
00:31:43.837 --> 00:31:46.454
Nothing. He just said
you owed him money.

401
00:31:46.524 --> 00:31:48.214
Not why?
Nothing else?

402
00:31:48.282 --> 00:31:49.362
Nothing.

403
00:31:49.433 --> 00:31:50.808
Why?
How much you owe him?

404
00:31:50.874 --> 00:31:52.880
None of your
goddamn business.

405
00:31:52.953 --> 00:31:55.797
I just got the feeling
he'd like to kill you...

406
00:31:55.861 --> 00:31:57.289
that's all.

407
00:31:57.365 --> 00:31:59.305
Oh. Christ.

408
00:31:59.380 --> 00:32:01.069
Porter.

409
00:32:06.128 --> 00:32:07.022
What?

410
00:32:07.088 --> 00:32:09.093
What did you tell him?

411
00:32:09.166 --> 00:32:10.791
Nothin'.

412
00:32:10.861 --> 00:32:12.267
What could I tell him?

413
00:32:12.332 --> 00:32:13.509
You tell him
about the money?

414
00:32:13.579 --> 00:32:14.527
The heroin?

415
00:32:14.603 --> 00:32:16.358
He had it with him.

416
00:32:16.426 --> 00:32:18.083
I told him I delivered it.

417
00:32:18.153 --> 00:32:19.331
You didn't tell him
nothin' else?

418
00:32:19.400 --> 00:32:21.308
I don't know nothin' else.

419
00:32:21.383 --> 00:32:23.999
Nah. You gave him
something.

420
00:32:24.069 --> 00:32:25.083
A name. maybe.

421
00:32:25.156 --> 00:32:26.944
Someone who knows
where to find me.

422
00:32:27.011 --> 00:32:28.439
I swear. Val.
on my mother--

423
00:32:28.514 --> 00:32:29.757
Hey. fuck your mother!

424
00:32:29.825 --> 00:32:32.758
Hey. that's not nice.
Try to take it easy.

425
00:32:32.832 --> 00:32:34.488
What the fuck
you looking at?

426
00:32:34.558 --> 00:32:35.899
Take it easy.
Not again.

427
00:32:35.965 --> 00:32:37.143
Huh?

428
00:32:37.213 --> 00:32:38.554
What the fuck
you looking at?

429
00:32:38.620 --> 00:32:39.863
No. Val. not again.

430
00:32:39.931 --> 00:32:41.718
What the fuck
are you looking at?

431
00:32:41.786 --> 00:32:42.899
Val. come on. don't.
Not again.

432
00:32:42.970 --> 00:32:45.749
Manager: Is there
some trouble here?

433
00:32:45.815 --> 00:32:48.781
No. We're just--
We're leaving.

434
00:32:48.854 --> 00:32:50.098
You know what. Val?

435
00:32:50.165 --> 00:32:51.920
This one's on me. OK?

436
00:32:51.988 --> 00:32:54.354
You see me reaching
for my fucking wallet?

437
00:32:54.418 --> 00:32:55.662
No.

438
00:32:58.160 --> 00:32:59.141
Sorry.

439
00:32:59.214 --> 00:33:00.839
He just got
a promotion...

440
00:33:00.910 --> 00:33:02.916
so he's
a little tense.

441
00:33:04.012 --> 00:33:06.182
Hey. pal. is there
a Michael here?

442
00:33:06.251 --> 00:33:07.461
That's him
over yonder.

443
00:33:09.706 --> 00:33:10.929
Michael.

444
00:33:11.058 --> 00:33:13.030
I'm told you're
the man to see...

445
00:33:13.104 --> 00:33:15.110
about expensive
horizontal refreshment.

446
00:33:15.183 --> 00:33:17.898
I'm looking for a girl
named Rosie.

447
00:33:17.965 --> 00:33:20.233
Prostitution is illegal...

448
00:33:20.301 --> 00:33:21.860
and you're speaking Greek.

449
00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:26.462
Usually these matters...

450
00:33:26.536 --> 00:33:29.153
are conducted
with more discretion.

451
00:33:31.622 --> 00:33:32.897
Aah!

452
00:33:32.965 --> 00:33:34.141
Be discreet now.

453
00:33:39.264 --> 00:33:40.824
What was her name again?

454
00:33:40.895 --> 00:33:41.910
Rosie.

455
00:33:41.982 --> 00:33:43.508
And who should I say
is looking for her?

456
00:33:43.582 --> 00:33:44.563
Just call her.

457
00:33:53.975 --> 00:33:55.184
- Rosie?
- Yeah.

458
00:33:55.254 --> 00:33:56.944
Give me the phone.

459
00:33:57.014 --> 00:33:58.256
Here.

460
00:33:58.325 --> 00:34:00.331
Take care of that.

461
00:34:02.002 --> 00:34:02.895
Rosie.

462
00:34:02.961 --> 00:34:04.488
Who the hell is this?

463
00:34:04.560 --> 00:34:05.575
Porter.

464
00:34:05.648 --> 00:34:08.843
Try again. honey.
Porter's dead.

465
00:34:08.910 --> 00:34:10.567
I used to drive for you...

466
00:34:10.638 --> 00:34:13.319
provide a safe
work environment.

467
00:34:13.388 --> 00:34:14.467
Porter?

468
00:34:16.041 --> 00:34:17.350
Yeah.

469
00:34:27.523 --> 00:34:30.422
Why pour salt
on old wounds?

470
00:34:31.456 --> 00:34:32.884
I didn't need to.

471
00:34:35.678 --> 00:34:38.524
I guess I had
a soft spot for her.

472
00:34:55.504 --> 00:34:57.293
Hi.

473
00:35:01.166 --> 00:35:02.376
Come on. Come in.

474
00:35:03.853 --> 00:35:06.372
You look pretty good
for a dead guy.

475
00:35:12.071 --> 00:35:14.459
How'd you hear about it?

476
00:35:14.534 --> 00:35:16.126
People who know
were talking.

477
00:35:16.198 --> 00:35:19.327
Plus. I heard your wife
was back in town alone.

478
00:35:20.674 --> 00:35:21.851
She's dead.

479
00:35:23.265 --> 00:35:24.889
I'm sorry. Porter.

480
00:35:26.079 --> 00:35:27.256
Why?

481
00:35:28.573 --> 00:35:30.775
Jesus. Surly Porter.

482
00:35:30.844 --> 00:35:33.176
You're the same
as ever. aren't you?

483
00:35:36.216 --> 00:35:37.939
This doesn't
look like you.

484
00:35:39.159 --> 00:35:40.565
Yeah. well.
people change.

485
00:35:42.613 --> 00:35:45.361
Stay. It's OK. baby.
It's OK.

486
00:35:45.428 --> 00:35:47.433
Come on. sweetheart.
It's OK.

487
00:35:47.505 --> 00:35:49.925
Meet the nastiest damn dog
who ever lived.

488
00:35:52.783 --> 00:35:53.960
What's his name?

489
00:35:54.029 --> 00:35:55.687
Porter.

490
00:35:57.100 --> 00:35:59.137
He took your job
after you left.

491
00:35:59.210 --> 00:36:00.355
He's just as tough...

492
00:36:00.426 --> 00:36:02.880
but he won't leave me.
will you. baby?

493
00:36:10.820 --> 00:36:12.128
I need a favor.

494
00:36:13.506 --> 00:36:15.098
A favor?

495
00:36:15.169 --> 00:36:17.339
Maybe you're not
the same as ever.

496
00:36:19.902 --> 00:36:21.756
I'm looking
for a syndicate boy.

497
00:36:23.196 --> 00:36:24.657
It's the "outfit." baby.

498
00:36:24.730 --> 00:36:26.323
We don't say
"syndicate" anymore.

499
00:36:26.394 --> 00:36:27.767
You know what I mean.

500
00:36:27.833 --> 00:36:29.621
Whatever the hell
you call it.

501
00:36:29.688 --> 00:36:32.053
Don't get touchy. Porter.
What's his name?

502
00:36:33.366 --> 00:36:34.707
Val Resnick.

503
00:36:36.981 --> 00:36:38.866
Oh.
that son of a bitch.

504
00:36:40.402 --> 00:36:41.578
You know him?

505
00:36:41.648 --> 00:36:46.185
Yeah. I met up with him
once a few years ago.

506
00:36:46.254 --> 00:36:48.108
He can't use
Star Service anymore...

507
00:36:48.173 --> 00:36:50.059
because he beats up
all the girls...

508
00:36:50.123 --> 00:36:52.358
and he almost killed one.

509
00:36:52.426 --> 00:36:53.538
You?

510
00:36:57.927 --> 00:36:59.170
Does it matter?

511
00:36:59.239 --> 00:37:01.278
You quit looking
after me. remember?

512
00:37:04.611 --> 00:37:06.781
Would you happen
to have a line...

513
00:37:06.849 --> 00:37:08.408
on where
he might be?

514
00:37:10.783 --> 00:37:12.756
I suppose
he's at the hotel.

515
00:37:12.830 --> 00:37:13.943
Which one?

516
00:37:14.013 --> 00:37:16.150
The outfit hotel.
They're all there.

517
00:37:17.275 --> 00:37:18.485
You got an address?

518
00:37:20.984 --> 00:37:22.772
We're friends. right?

519
00:37:22.840 --> 00:37:24.727
I mean. we used to be.

520
00:37:24.791 --> 00:37:28.236
But I'm an employee. too.
and I don't think the outfit...

521
00:37:28.308 --> 00:37:30.695
would like me telling you
where the hotel was. would they?

522
00:37:30.770 --> 00:37:32.493
No. What do you
think I'm gonna do?

523
00:37:32.562 --> 00:37:33.738
How strong are you.
Porter?

524
00:37:33.808 --> 00:37:35.979
Personally. I think
you are the strongest man...

525
00:37:36.048 --> 00:37:37.258
I have ever met.

526
00:37:37.328 --> 00:37:39.399
But I wonder
if it's enough.

527
00:37:39.470 --> 00:37:40.930
For what?

528
00:37:41.005 --> 00:37:42.411
If I know you...

529
00:37:42.476 --> 00:37:44.678
you want this Resnick guy
for something he won't like.

530
00:37:44.746 --> 00:37:46.720
Yeah.
I'm gonna kill him.

531
00:37:49.895 --> 00:37:51.684
That's something
he won't like.

532
00:37:53.062 --> 00:37:55.906
What if something goes wrong.
and they grab you...

533
00:37:55.970 --> 00:37:58.074
and they ask you where you
found out about the hotel?

534
00:37:58.145 --> 00:37:59.486
Why are we even
talking about this?

535
00:37:59.553 --> 00:38:00.894
You know I wouldn't
turn you in.

536
00:38:00.961 --> 00:38:02.716
I wouldn't talk about
who told me what.

537
00:38:02.783 --> 00:38:04.124
But what if they
ask you hard?

538
00:38:05.565 --> 00:38:09.010
I'll--I'll tell them it was
a cab dispatcher named Stegman.

539
00:38:13.049 --> 00:38:15.731
The Oakwood Arms.
Union and 17th.

540
00:38:46.082 --> 00:38:47.195
Hi. Val.

541
00:38:49.569 --> 00:38:51.160
Where's my money?

542
00:38:56.701 --> 00:38:58.641
No. it's not there.
I took your gun.

543
00:38:58.715 --> 00:38:59.827
It's back here.

544
00:38:59.899 --> 00:39:01.424
You look like a pro.

545
00:39:01.497 --> 00:39:03.057
You keep
your mouth shut...

546
00:39:03.129 --> 00:39:05.016
and you'll walk
out of here.

547
00:39:07.798 --> 00:39:10.131
My 70 grand--
I want it.

548
00:39:11.603 --> 00:39:14.089
I don't have it
right now.

549
00:39:14.161 --> 00:39:15.208
Where is it?

550
00:39:15.281 --> 00:39:19.174
I gave all 130.000
to the outfit.

551
00:39:19.246 --> 00:39:21.034
I gave it all to them.

552
00:39:21.103 --> 00:39:22.345
Well...

553
00:39:22.413 --> 00:39:25.956
tell them you gave them money
that doesn't belong to you...

554
00:39:26.026 --> 00:39:27.105
and get it back.

555
00:39:27.177 --> 00:39:28.899
Now. Porter.
I can't do that.

556
00:39:28.969 --> 00:39:30.692
I mean. you don't
know these guy--

557
00:39:30.760 --> 00:39:34.434
You're gonna kill me whether
I get the money or not.

558
00:39:35.557 --> 00:39:38.140
All right. I'll get it.
I'll get the money.

559
00:39:38.211 --> 00:39:40.097
Just give me a few days.
all right?

560
00:39:40.161 --> 00:39:41.437
What the fuck
are you doing?

561
00:39:42.496 --> 00:39:45.561
Noon. Tomorrow.
Say it.

562
00:39:45.631 --> 00:39:46.612
All right.

563
00:39:46.686 --> 00:39:48.857
You know. this may
sound crazy. Porter...

564
00:39:48.926 --> 00:39:50.810
but. uh. no hard
feelings. huh?

565
00:39:50.874 --> 00:39:53.362
I did what I had to do.

566
00:39:53.433 --> 00:39:54.926
You could appreciate that.

567
00:39:55.001 --> 00:39:56.407
Yeah. I appreciate that.
you--

568
00:39:56.472 --> 00:39:57.813
No. no. no. Don't.

569
00:39:59.414 --> 00:40:02.609
Please. Allow me.

570
00:40:09.136 --> 00:40:11.273
Jesus.

571
00:40:11.343 --> 00:40:12.390
God.

572
00:40:17.675 --> 00:40:18.689
God.

573
00:40:19.818 --> 00:40:21.410
You bitch!

574
00:40:22.600 --> 00:40:24.738
Let her work.

575
00:40:37.152 --> 00:40:39.539
Me love you. baby.

576
00:40:41.532 --> 00:40:43.920
Me love you long... time.

577
00:40:49.943 --> 00:40:51.317
Wait up. hon. Wait.

578
00:40:57.202 --> 00:40:58.412
Tomorrow.

579
00:40:58.482 --> 00:41:00.422
Noon.
You and the money...

580
00:41:00.497 --> 00:41:03.016
be at the corner
of 7th and Franklin...

581
00:41:03.087 --> 00:41:04.069
at the pay phone.

582
00:41:05.679 --> 00:41:06.920
OK.

583
00:41:06.989 --> 00:41:08.395
OK.

584
00:41:09.867 --> 00:41:11.622
Where'd you get this?

585
00:41:11.690 --> 00:41:12.803
Hmm?

586
00:41:12.873 --> 00:41:15.327
Some hooker had it
on her shelf.

587
00:41:15.400 --> 00:41:18.115
I recognized you. I swiped it
in case I could use it.

588
00:41:18.182 --> 00:41:19.360
Did you hurt her?

589
00:41:19.430 --> 00:41:20.540
Huh?

590
00:41:20.612 --> 00:41:22.716
The hooker--
did you hurt her?

591
00:41:22.787 --> 00:41:24.575
What does that
have to do with anything?

592
00:41:24.642 --> 00:41:25.983
Tell me quick

593
00:41:27.776 --> 00:41:29.434
Oh. ain't love a kick

594
00:41:31.902 --> 00:41:33.177
Tell me quick

595
00:41:33.244 --> 00:41:36.178
I've got a few minutes.

596
00:41:36.251 --> 00:41:37.559
So go boil an egg.

597
00:41:37.626 --> 00:41:39.119
In the head

598
00:41:40.953 --> 00:41:41.845
Uhh!

599
00:41:44.790 --> 00:41:47.090
Philip tells me
you have a problem...

600
00:41:47.156 --> 00:41:48.530
you need help with.

601
00:41:48.595 --> 00:41:50.896
Yes. sir.

602
00:41:50.962 --> 00:41:53.230
Is it your problem who
breached our security...

603
00:41:53.297 --> 00:41:54.790
last night
at the Oakwood?

604
00:41:54.864 --> 00:41:56.270
Yes. sir. Ahem.

605
00:41:56.335 --> 00:41:57.992
Then he breaks
into my apartment--

606
00:41:58.062 --> 00:41:59.270
There's
an old expression...

607
00:41:59.340 --> 00:42:02.056
that has
served me well.

608
00:42:02.123 --> 00:42:04.358
"Do not shit
where you eat."

609
00:42:06.057 --> 00:42:07.136
Or "live."

610
00:42:07.208 --> 00:42:09.411
"Do not shit
where you live."

611
00:42:09.479 --> 00:42:11.517
Yeah.
I like that better.

612
00:42:11.589 --> 00:42:12.570
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. Mr.Carter.

613
00:42:12.644 --> 00:42:15.424
There are 3 ways that
we can handle this.

614
00:42:15.491 --> 00:42:17.726
1 - We can help you.

615
00:42:17.793 --> 00:42:20.029
2 - We can allow you
to help yourself.

616
00:42:20.097 --> 00:42:23.324
And 3 - We can
have you replaced.

617
00:42:28.154 --> 00:42:30.161
We have an investment
in you. Resnick...

618
00:42:30.234 --> 00:42:33.298
of time. money.
and training...

619
00:42:33.369 --> 00:42:36.433
so assisting you
would be. in a way...

620
00:42:36.503 --> 00:42:38.922
protecting our investment.

621
00:42:38.997 --> 00:42:42.094
And that is always
good business policy.

622
00:42:42.162 --> 00:42:43.852
Yes. sir.
Yes. sir. Mr.Carter.

623
00:42:43.921 --> 00:42:46.669
Thank you. sir.
You won't regret it.

624
00:42:46.736 --> 00:42:47.913
Now...

625
00:42:49.423 --> 00:42:50.697
according to Philip...

626
00:42:50.765 --> 00:42:53.579
a man has come to town
to kill you?

627
00:42:53.644 --> 00:42:54.537
Yes.

628
00:42:54.604 --> 00:42:55.879
And you say
that he's alone...

629
00:42:55.947 --> 00:42:57.800
and that he's a professional robber...

630
00:42:57.865 --> 00:42:58.792
is that correct?

631
00:42:58.856 --> 00:43:00.677
Yes. sir. He does
payroll jobs. banks...

632
00:43:00.744 --> 00:43:02.019
you know. stuff like that.

633
00:43:02.086 --> 00:43:04.801
Mm-hmm.
What's his name?

634
00:43:04.869 --> 00:43:06.525
Porter.

635
00:43:06.596 --> 00:43:08.155
Well. what's
his first name?

636
00:43:13.376 --> 00:43:15.546
You know. I don't know it.

637
00:43:15.613 --> 00:43:17.882
He never called himself
anything but Porter.

638
00:43:20.155 --> 00:43:21.201
Mmm.

639
00:43:28.886 --> 00:43:32.397
Where did you
get the $130.000?

640
00:43:36.689 --> 00:43:39.820
That's why this man
has come to town. huh?

641
00:43:39.888 --> 00:43:42.700
The $130.000
that you paid us back?

642
00:43:42.765 --> 00:43:45.383
Yes. sir. but only
70.000 of it was his.

643
00:43:45.452 --> 00:43:47.753
Well. we never asked you
where you got the money.

644
00:43:47.819 --> 00:43:49.793
It's none of
our business...

645
00:43:49.866 --> 00:43:53.725
but now it appears it
has become our business.

646
00:43:55.653 --> 00:43:58.237
Here's his file.
Mr.Carter.

647
00:44:06.048 --> 00:44:07.574
Do you understand
your value...

648
00:44:07.646 --> 00:44:09.587
to the organization.
Resnick?

649
00:44:12.156 --> 00:44:13.268
You're a sadist.

650
00:44:13.338 --> 00:44:15.509
You lack compunction.
That comes in handy.

651
00:44:17.368 --> 00:44:19.440
But now you've
allowed an area...

652
00:44:19.511 --> 00:44:22.575
of your personal life
to become a danger to us.

653
00:44:25.172 --> 00:44:27.887
A man in our organization
needs to be tough...

654
00:44:27.954 --> 00:44:30.288
and self-reliant.

655
00:44:30.353 --> 00:44:35.204
Were you to handle
this problem on your own...

656
00:44:35.277 --> 00:44:37.643
there would be no doubt...

657
00:44:37.709 --> 00:44:40.195
that you're the kind
of man we want.

658
00:44:40.267 --> 00:44:41.989
I want to. Ahem.

659
00:44:42.058 --> 00:44:44.610
I want to handle it
myself. Mr.Carter.

660
00:44:44.681 --> 00:44:46.305
Great.

661
00:44:46.375 --> 00:44:47.617
Until the matter
is handled...

662
00:44:47.686 --> 00:44:51.808
I want you to move out
of the Oakwood Arms.

663
00:44:51.876 --> 00:44:54.689
Uh. ahem. but I don't
have a place. uh--

664
00:44:54.754 --> 00:44:57.403
I don't want anymore
unpleasantness at the hotel.

665
00:44:59.295 --> 00:45:00.755
Yes. sir.

666
00:45:08.505 --> 00:45:10.676
Excuse me for saying so.
Mr.Carter...

667
00:45:10.744 --> 00:45:13.524
but it might be easier
if Resnick just disappeared.

668
00:45:14.805 --> 00:45:17.193
I thought about that...

669
00:45:17.268 --> 00:45:19.721
but I'm not worried
about Resnick.

670
00:45:19.794 --> 00:45:22.826
He wouldn't last 2 minutes
out on the street without us.

671
00:45:22.897 --> 00:45:25.067
It's that other mutt
I'm thinking about.

672
00:45:25.134 --> 00:45:26.083
What's his name?

673
00:45:26.158 --> 00:45:27.140
Porter.

674
00:45:29.228 --> 00:45:31.616
Takes a lot of moxie to walk
right into the outfit...

675
00:45:31.692 --> 00:45:33.600
and start whacking
our guys around.

676
00:45:34.729 --> 00:45:36.658
Either that.
or he's shit nuts.

677
00:45:36.786 --> 00:45:40.974
Frankly. I don't understand it
for $130.000.

678
00:45:41.040 --> 00:45:43.243
70.000. His share.

679
00:45:43.311 --> 00:45:46.505
That's even worse.

680
00:45:46.573 --> 00:45:49.734
I don't want Mr.Bronson
hearing about this.

681
00:45:49.802 --> 00:45:52.103
He'll think
I'm getting soft.

682
00:45:52.169 --> 00:45:53.990
One of his principles
has always been...

683
00:45:54.056 --> 00:45:56.870
"If you don't understand it.
get rid of it."

684
00:45:58.086 --> 00:46:01.084
A stitch in time.
so to speak. so...

685
00:46:02.180 --> 00:46:03.933
stitch this mutt up. Phil.

686
00:46:08.766 --> 00:46:11.253
Any Polaroids
or trophies?

687
00:46:11.326 --> 00:46:12.601
No. not this time.

688
00:46:14.109 --> 00:46:15.830
- Yeah?

689
00:46:15.898 --> 00:46:18.264
They cut me loose.
Pearl.

690
00:46:18.329 --> 00:46:19.572
Just like I thought
they would.

691
00:46:19.640 --> 00:46:21.908
Hold on one second.

692
00:46:21.975 --> 00:46:23.698
Shut up!

693
00:46:23.766 --> 00:46:25.869
I'm on
the fucking phone!

694
00:46:35.374 --> 00:46:36.421
Yes?

695
00:46:36.494 --> 00:46:38.532
Did your friends
make it to town?

696
00:46:38.605 --> 00:46:40.776
Oh. yeah.
Last night. baby.

697
00:46:40.844 --> 00:46:42.696
Good. Now.
did you tell them...

698
00:46:42.761 --> 00:46:44.648
it was Porter
took their payroll?

699
00:46:44.713 --> 00:46:46.370
I did.

700
00:46:46.439 --> 00:46:48.446
And they want
retribution.

701
00:46:48.518 --> 00:46:51.200
All right. All right.
here's what we do.

702
00:47:06.619 --> 00:47:09.934
Well. I'll stand up
next to a mountain

703
00:47:10.010 --> 00:47:13.008
And I'll chop it down
with the edge of my hand

704
00:47:51.889 --> 00:47:53.190
Yeah.
that's Porter.

705
00:47:53.256 --> 00:47:55.077
He's shit
for brains.

706
00:47:56.143 --> 00:47:57.768
Oh. shit.

707
00:48:18.495 --> 00:48:20.283
Shit!

708
00:48:21.963 --> 00:48:23.456
Next time. Porter.

709
00:48:27.432 --> 00:48:29.602
Looks like Porter's
made some new friends.

710
00:48:48.218 --> 00:48:49.145
Easy. mister.

711
00:48:49.210 --> 00:48:51.031
I'm OK. I don't want
to press charges.

712
00:48:51.097 --> 00:48:52.144
Who were they.
huh. pal?

713
00:48:52.216 --> 00:48:53.622
I don't know.
I don't know.

714
00:48:53.687 --> 00:48:54.581
Oh. man.

715
00:48:54.647 --> 00:48:56.305
Oh. it's you guys.

716
00:48:56.374 --> 00:48:57.867
Our buddy Stegman
says you got a line...

717
00:48:57.942 --> 00:48:59.184
on a load of cash
there. Porter.

718
00:48:59.251 --> 00:49:01.040
250 grand.
to be exact.

719
00:49:02.226 --> 00:49:03.370
70.

720
00:49:04.625 --> 00:49:06.185
Come on. man.
Get off of me.

721
00:49:06.256 --> 00:49:07.815
All right. all right.
all right.

722
00:49:07.888 --> 00:49:09.097
What do you
take us for. huh?

723
00:49:09.167 --> 00:49:10.923
Idiots?

724
00:49:10.990 --> 00:49:13.159
Nobody'd go through all
this shit for 70 grand.

725
00:49:13.227 --> 00:49:14.274
We don't like trouble.
buddy.

726
00:49:14.347 --> 00:49:16.102
You look like a whole bunch
of trouble to us.

727
00:49:16.170 --> 00:49:18.209
We found a dead girl
full of heroin.

728
00:49:18.281 --> 00:49:19.741
There were signs
of a struggle...

729
00:49:19.816 --> 00:49:21.954
and the coroner's
not so sure it was an O.D.

730
00:49:22.023 --> 00:49:23.648
We got a witness.
though.

731
00:49:23.718 --> 00:49:25.624
A guy with only one
nostril. Remember him?

732
00:49:25.700 --> 00:49:26.877
Uh-huh.

733
00:49:26.946 --> 00:49:27.895
Hey. don't worry.
Porter.

734
00:49:27.970 --> 00:49:29.432
We're gonna give you
immunity.

735
00:49:29.506 --> 00:49:31.773
Room to operate.
"Get Out of Jail Free" card.

736
00:49:31.841 --> 00:49:34.457
All you got to do
is get the money.

737
00:49:34.526 --> 00:49:37.273
Oh. we can't
help you. though.

738
00:49:37.341 --> 00:49:38.769
It'd be against the law.

739
00:49:38.844 --> 00:49:39.956
You understand.
Porter?

740
00:49:41.690 --> 00:49:42.770
It's my money.

741
00:49:42.842 --> 00:49:44.019
Wrong. Porter.

742
00:49:44.089 --> 00:49:46.357
Huh?

743
00:49:46.424 --> 00:49:47.884
It's our money. Porter.

744
00:49:47.959 --> 00:49:49.648
Me and my partner's money.

745
00:49:49.718 --> 00:49:51.724
You be a good boy.
we'll give you a piece.

746
00:49:51.796 --> 00:49:53.005
We'll be easy.
Porter.

747
00:49:53.076 --> 00:49:55.278
You got it?

748
00:49:55.346 --> 00:49:56.273
Yeah. he's got it.

749
00:49:56.337 --> 00:49:57.351
You understand?

750
00:49:58.448 --> 00:49:59.757
You take it easy. huh?
We'll be in touch.

751
00:49:59.823 --> 00:50:01.349
Sure. thanks.

752
00:50:01.423 --> 00:50:02.763
What a dope.

753
00:50:03.980 --> 00:50:04.874
Fuck.

754
00:50:04.940 --> 00:50:06.848
Crooked cops.

755
00:50:06.923 --> 00:50:08.678
Did they come
any other way?

756
00:50:09.898 --> 00:50:12.100
If I had been just
a little dumber...

757
00:50:12.168 --> 00:50:15.645
I could have joined
the force myself.

758
00:50:44.596 --> 00:50:45.740
Jesus Christ. Porter...

759
00:50:45.811 --> 00:50:47.403
you need to see
a doctor.

760
00:50:47.474 --> 00:50:49.067
Yeah.

761
00:50:49.137 --> 00:50:50.065
It's gonna sting.

762
00:50:50.129 --> 00:50:52.680
Just clean it up.
all right?

763
00:50:52.751 --> 00:50:53.960
You hold it there.

764
00:50:54.029 --> 00:50:55.110
Yeah. right.

765
00:51:07.206 --> 00:51:08.415
I'll do it.

766
00:51:14.018 --> 00:51:15.577
Tell me something.
Porter.

767
00:51:17.440 --> 00:51:19.381
When did you decide
to leave?

768
00:51:19.455 --> 00:51:21.689
Was it that night
we slept together?

769
00:51:23.548 --> 00:51:25.140
No.

770
00:51:25.210 --> 00:51:29.299
It was the next day
when I had to drive you to work.

771
00:51:33.909 --> 00:51:36.117
You could have
asked me to quit.

772
00:51:40.787 --> 00:51:43.916
You could have asked me
to drive you somewhere else.

773
00:51:56.905 --> 00:51:59.042
Hubba hubba hubba.

774
00:52:07.107 --> 00:52:07.903
Thanks.

775
00:52:07.969 --> 00:52:09.791
Does it fit?

776
00:52:09.857 --> 00:52:11.579
Oh. yeah...

777
00:52:11.648 --> 00:52:13.751
like it was made for me.

778
00:52:15.005 --> 00:52:16.826
It'll look great
in your casket.

779
00:52:27.638 --> 00:52:29.491
You know what I think?

780
00:52:29.556 --> 00:52:31.246
I think that. uh...

781
00:52:31.315 --> 00:52:34.445
all those stories about
you being dead were true.

782
00:52:34.514 --> 00:52:36.521
You're just too thick-headed
to admit it.

783
00:53:03.648 --> 00:53:06.548
Porter.
God. I missed you.

784
00:53:06.621 --> 00:53:08.279
I missed you.

785
00:53:16.184 --> 00:53:18.038
Don't talk. Don't.

786
00:53:18.103 --> 00:53:19.150
Oh. no. I...

787
00:53:19.222 --> 00:53:20.301
I can't.

788
00:53:20.373 --> 00:53:22.861
I got. uh...

789
00:53:23.892 --> 00:53:24.906
stuff to do.

790
00:53:24.979 --> 00:53:26.636
I got...

791
00:53:32.014 --> 00:53:33.126
Ahem.

792
00:54:07.608 --> 00:54:08.502
Porter.

793
00:54:15.764 --> 00:54:17.291
Where is he?

794
00:54:20.561 --> 00:54:22.894
Porter.
Where is he?

795
00:54:22.959 --> 00:54:24.649
He's in the bedroom.

796
00:54:39.749 --> 00:54:41.276
Is he hurt bad?

797
00:54:41.348 --> 00:54:42.558
Hmm?

798
00:54:42.628 --> 00:54:45.276
The doctor
should be here any minute.

799
00:54:45.345 --> 00:54:46.839
No. That's bullshit.

800
00:55:00.856 --> 00:55:04.498
Porter. here I come.
pally.

801
00:55:04.566 --> 00:55:06.387
- Porter!

802
00:55:06.453 --> 00:55:08.078
Hey!

